                <p ng-show="button1">I remember my first rappel.  I was 14 and we had set up a rope in an old quarry.  I hiked to the top and stood in line, however when my time came I chickened out.  By the end of the day I still had not rappelled.  The leader was about to take the ropes down when I finally got the courage to commit.  I grabbed the rope and threaded it between my legs, across my chest, and down over my back.  What a thrill.  I have never looked back, although I still look down and check before I commit to a rappel.<figure ng-show="button1"><img src="images/rappel.jpg" width="300"><figcaption>note: not me</figcaption></figure></p>
                 
